eblower, [[Li Wenliang]], had not committed the crime of spreading \"rumors\" when on 30 December 2019 he posted to a WeChat forum for medical school alumni that seven patients under his care appeared to have contracted SARS.  In their ruling, the Supreme People's Court stated, \"If society had at the time believed those 'rumours', and wore masks, used disinfectant and avoided going to the wildlife market as if there were a SARS outbreak, perhaps it would've meant we could better control the coronavirus today,\" the court said. \"Rumours end when there is openness.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.caixinglobal.com/2020-01-31/after-being-punished-by-local-police-coronavirus-whistleblower-vindicated-by-top-court-101509986.html|website=www.caixinglobal.com|access-date=2020-02-08|title=Whistleblower Li Wenliang: There Should Be More Than One Voice In A Healthy Society|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205002435/https://www.caixinglobal.com/2020-01-31/after-being-punished-by-local-police-coronavirus-whistleblower-vindicated-by-top-court-101509986.html|archive-date=2020-02-05|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/ETgXN6HInzlC8cxzhDdU9g|script-title=zh:\u6cbb\u7406\u6709\u5173\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e\u7684\u8c23\u8a00\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u8fd9\u7bc7\u6587\u7ae0\u8bf4\u6e05\u695a\u4e86!|trans-title=Regarding the issue of authorities handling the new novel coronavirus as rumours|publisher=[[Supreme People's Court]]|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202004701/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/ETgXN6HInzlC8cxzhDdU9g|archive-date=2020-02-02|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 8:<ref>{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200128-sitrep-8-ncov-cleared.pdf?sfvrsn=8b671ce5_2|title=Novel Coronavirus(2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 8|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202195554/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200128-sitrep-8-ncov-cleared.pdf?sfvrsn=8b671ce5_2|archive-date=2020-02-02|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThailand confirms six more cases, bringing the total infected there to 14. Thailand's health minister, [[Anutin Charnvirakul]], states that \"we are not able to stop the spread\" of coronavirus in the country.<ref name=\"auto11\">{{cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/thailand-not-able-to-stop-the-spread-of-new-coronavirus-11919860|title=Thailand 'not able to stop the spread' of new coronavirus|website=Sky News|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202160111/https://news.sky.com/story/thailand-not-able-to-stop-the-spread-of-new-coronavirus-11919860|archive-date=2020-02-02|url-status=live}}</ref> Singapore confirms two more cases, bringing the total infected in Singapore to seven. That was followed by a Hubei-related suspension from 29 January.<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-7-confirmed-cases-in-singapore-no-entry-or-transit-for-new-visitors-with-hubei|title=Wuhan virus: 2 new confirmed cases in Singapore, bringing total to 7; no entry or transit for new visitors from Hubei|website=The Straits Times|accessdate=28 January 2020|date=28 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128094942/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/wuhan-virus-7-confirmed-cases-in-singapore-no-entry-or-transit-for-new-visitors-with-hubei|archive-date=28 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Japan confirms 3 additional cases, bringing the total infected in Japan to seven, including a man who had never visited Wuhan. He was working as a tour bus driver and had driven a group from Wuhan earlier in January.<ref name=\"auto8\">{{cite web|url=https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2020/01/e8f47252a245-urgent-japan-sees-1st-coronavirus-case-not-linked-to-recent-travel-to-china.html|title=Japan sees 1st coronavirus case not linked to recent travel to China|date=28 January 2020|via=Kyodo News|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129162636/https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2020/01/e8f47252a245-urgent-japan-sees-1st-coronavirus-case-not-linked-to-recent-travel-to-china.html|archive-date=29 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto10\">{{cite web|url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2020/01/28/national/japan-charter-flights-evacuate-japanese-virus-wuhan-china/#.XjAFCLdlB-E|title=Japan reports new coronavirus cases as it moves to evacuate nationals from Wuhan|date=28 January 2020|via=The Japan Times|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128134009/https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2020/01/28/national/japan-charter-flights-evacuate-japanese-virus-wuhan-china/#.XjAFCLdlB-E|archive-date=28 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Germany's first confirmed case, reported the previous day, had occurred in a German citizen who had not travelled to China. However, he had close contact with a visiting Chinese colleague who reported starting to feel ill during her return flight to Shanghai and she was diagnosed with coronavirus infection after arriving in China. Germany confirmed 3 new cases, all of whom were coworkers of the first confirmed patient.<ref name=\"auto6\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sueddeutsche.de/gesundheit/coronavirus-drei-weitere-infizierte-in-bayern-1.4776016|title=Drei weitere Infizierte in Bayern|last=Zeitung|first=S\u00fcddeutsche|website=S\u00fcddeutsche.de|language=de|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref> France confirmed its fourth case, an elderly Chinese tourist who is in critical condition.<ref name=\"auto5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/fr/20200128-nouveau-coronavirus-quatri%C3%A8me-cas-en-france-le-patient-en-r%C3%A9animation|title=Quatri\u00e8me cas en France, le patient en r\u00e9animation|last=|first=|date=|website=Franceinfo|language=fr|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref>\n\nThe Brazilian [[Ministry of Health (Brazil)|Ministry of Health]] reports three suspected cases ongoing in three locations: [[Belo Horizonte]] (MG), [[Curitiba]] (PR) and [[S\u00e3o Leopoldo]] (RS).<ref name=\"auto7\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/01/28/brasil-tem-2-novos-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-em-porto-alegre-e-curitiba-ministerio.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 2 novos casos suspeitos de coronav\u00edrus em S\u00e3o Leopoldo e em Curitiba, diz Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade|website=G1|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131042625/https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/01/28/brasil-tem-2-novos-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-em-porto-alegre-e-curitiba-ministerio.ghtml|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref> Canada reports a new presumptive case in [[British Columbia]], a man in his 40s who had recently travelled to Wuhan.<ref name=\"auto12\">{{cite web|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6473048/bc-coronavirus-update-tuesday-jan-28/|title=First presumptive case of coronavirus confirmed in B.C.|website=Global News|language=en|access-date=2020-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128183227/https://globalnews.ca/news/6473048/bc-coronavirus-update-tuesday-jan-28/|archive-date=2020-01-28|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nA UK-Chinese medical research paper reports a statistical model finding that \"estimates suggest the actual number of infected cases could be much higher than the reported, with estimated 26,701 cases (as of 28th January 2020).\"<ref>{{cite journal|url=https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.01.27.922443v1|title=Breaking down of the healthcare system: Mathematical modelling for controlling the novel coronavirus (2019-nCoV) outbreak in Wuhan, China|first1=Wai-kit|last1=Ming|first2=Jian|last2=Huang|first3=Casper J. P.|last3=Zhang|date=28 January 2020|journal=bioRxiv|pages=2020.01.27.922443|via=www.biorxiv.org|doi=10.1101/2020.01.27.922443|access-date=8 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201160242/https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.01.27.922443v1|archive-date=1 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nScientists from The Peter Doherty Institute for Infection and Immunity (Doherty Institute) in Melbourne reported that they had successfully grown 2019-nCoV from a patient sample.<ref name=\"auto9\">{{cite web|url=https://www.doherty.edu.au/news-events/news/coronavirus|title=Doherty Institute scientists first to grow and share Wuhan coronavirus|last=|first=|date=|website=www.doherty.edu.au|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128203302/https://www.doherty.edu.au/news-events/news/coronavirus|archive-date=2020-01-28|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref>\n\n[[Xiangyang]] became quarantined starting 00:00;<ref name=\":101\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_5671283|title=\u8944\u9633\u706b\u8f66\u7ad9\u5173\u95ed\uff0c\u6e56\u5317\u7701\u6700\u540e\u4e00\u4e2a\u5730\u7ea7\u5e02\"\u5c01\u57ce\"_\u5a92\u4f53_\u6f8e\u6e43\u65b0\u95fb-The Paper|website=www.thepaper.cn|access-date=2020-02-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202170024/https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_5671283|archive-date=2020-02-02|url-status=live}}</ref> the entire Hubei province thus became quarantined save for [[Shennongjia Forestry District]].\n\n===29 January===\n'''WHO''' Situation Report 9:<ref name=\"auto13\">{{Citation|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200129-sitrep-9-ncov-v2.pdf?sfvrsn=e2c8915_2|title=Novel Coronavirus(2019-nCoV) Situation Report - 9|access-date=2020-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206035856/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200129-sitrep-9-ncov-v2.pdf?sfvrsn=e2c8915_2|archive-date=2020-02-06|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Tibet Autonomous Region|Tibet]] reported its first suspected case identified on the previous day<ref name=\"sina_tibet\">{{cite web|url=https://news.sina.com.cn/c/2020-01-29/doc-iihnzhha5188508.shtml|tit