\u6d77\u65b0\u589e7\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b|last=\u5065\u5eb7\u4e0a\u6d7712320|date=2020-01-23|website=news.sina.com.cn|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref> [[Xinjiang]] reported two laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/01/23/678507.html|title=\u65b0\u7586\u9996\u6b21\u786e\u8bca2\u4f8b\u8f93\u5165\u6027\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u75c5\u4f8b|last=www.bjnews.com.cn|website=www.bjnews.com.cn|access-date=2020-01-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200124063007/http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/01/23/678507.html|archive-date=2020-01-24|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Shaanxi]] reported three laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/01/23/678506.html|title=\u9655\u897f\u786e\u8bca3\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u80ba\u708e\u75c5\u4f8b|last=www.bjnews.com.cn|website=www.bjnews.com.cn|access-date=2020-01-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200124035900/http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/01/23/678506.html|archive-date=2020-01-24|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Gansu]] reported two laboratory-confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wsjk.gansu.gov.cn/single/10910/82997.html|title=\u7518\u8083\u7701\u786e\u8ba42\u4f8b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u7684\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128195957/http://wsjk.gansu.gov.cn/single/10910/82997.html|archive-date=28 January 2020|access-date=}}</ref> Macau also reported its second laboratory-confirmed case, another 66-year-old man from Wuhan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/article/3047337/macau-confirms-second-patient-infected-chinese-coronavirus|title=Macau confirms second patient infected with Wuhan virus|date=2020-01-23|website=South China Morning Post|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref> In all, the total number of laboratory-confirmed cases in mainland China increased to 628 while the death toll remained at 17.\n\n[[Singapore]] reported its first laboratory-confirmed case, a 66-year-old man from China.<ref name=\"Update23Jan\">{{cite web|last1=Goh|first1=Timothy|last2=Toh|first2=Ting Wei|title=Singapore confirms first case of Wuhan virus|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/singapore-confirms-first-case-of-wuhan-virus|website=The Straits Times|accessdate=23 January 2020|date=23 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200124014101/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/singapore-confirms-first-case-of-wuhan-virus|archive-date=24 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Vietnam]] confirmed its first two laboratory-confirmed cases, a 65 or 66-year-old father and 27 or 28-year-old son from China.<ref name=\"Vietnam23Jan2020\">{{cite news|url=https://e.vnexpress.net/news/news/vietnam-confirms-first-acute-pneumonia-cases-from-wuhan-virus-4046310.html|title=Vietnam confirms first acute pneumonia cases from Wuhan virus|date=23 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=Phan28Jan2020>{{Cite journal|doi= 10.1056/NEJMc2001272|pmid= 31991079|title= Importation and Human-to-Human Transmission of a Novel Coronavirus in Vietnam|year = 2020|last1 = Phan|first1 = Lan T.|last2 = Nguyen|first2 = Thuong V.|last3 = Luong|first3 = Quang C.|last4 = Nguyen|first4 = Thinh V.|last5 = Nguyen|first5 = Hieu T.|last6 = Le|first6 = Hung Q.|last7 = Nguyen|first7 = Thuc T.|last8 = Cao|first8 = Thang M.|last9 = Pham|first9 = Quang D.|journal = New England Journal of Medicine|volume = 382|issue = 9|pages = 872\u2013874}}</ref>\n\nA scientific preprint from the Wuhan institute of Virology is posted on [[Biorxiv]] (later published in ''[[Nature (journal)|Nature]]''<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-020-2012-7|title=A pneumonia outbreak associated with a new coronavirus of probable bat origin|first1=Peng|last1=Zhou|first2=Xing-Lou|last2=Yang|first3=Xian-Guang|last3=Wang|fi