ore, bringing tally to 13|date=30 January 2020|website=CNA|accessdate=30 January 2020}}</ref> South Korea confirms two more cases, with one of them being the first human-to-human transmission there.<ref>{{cite web|title=S. Korea reports 2 more cases of new coronavirus, 1st human transmission|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200130000905|website=The Korea Herald|accessdate=30 January 2020|language=en|date=30 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130153554/http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200130000905|archive-date=30 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Vietnam confirms three new cases, bringing the total to five.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://vietnamnews.vn/society/591638/first-vietnamese-citizens-test-positive-for-coronavirus.html|title=First Vietnamese citizens test positive for coronavirus|date=2020-01-30|website=vietnamnews.vn|accessdate=2020-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130143813/https://vietnamnews.vn/society/591638/first-vietnamese-citizens-test-positive-for-coronavirus.html|archive-date=2020-01-30|url-status=live}}</ref> France confirms its sixth case.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200130-france-confirms-sixth-case-of-coronavirus-infection-health-official-says|title=France confirms sixth case of coronavirus infection, health official says|date=2020-01-30|website=France 24|language=en|access-date=2020-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131023111/https://www.france24.com/en/20200130-france-confirms-sixth-case-of-coronavirus-infection-health-official-says|archive-date=2020-01-31|url-status=live}}</ref> Italy confirms its first two cases in a press conference by the Prime Minister, [[Giuseppe Conte]].<ref name=\"auto4\">{{cite web|url=http://news.trust.org/item/20200130210003-wm57y/|title=Two first coronavirus cases confirmed in Italy - prime minister|last=Foundation|first=Thomson Reuters|website=news.trust.org|access-date=2020-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/